      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here is the `detect_flakiness` function you requested. It runs the provided function multiple times and checks if the set of returned results contains more than one unique value. If there is more than one unique result across all runs, it indicates the test is exhibiting flakiness by returning different values.\n\n```python\ndef detect_flakiness(func, n_runs=10):\n    results = []\n    for _ in range(n_runs):\n        results.append(func())\n    return len(set(results)) > 1\n```",
